WorkRoles replaces the Work tab with role-based work management. No setup required, safe to remove if you don't like it.

Instead of assigning priority numbers, you assign a set of ordered roles to colonists. A role is simply a named set of ordered jobs. Priorities are calculated and set automatically behind the scenes.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mnmr/rw.workroles/main/images/feature-drag-drop.png[/img]

Set up a role once, hand it to any number of colonists, and adjust everyone by editing one list.

[h1]Key Features[/h1]
[list]
[*][b]No Priorities:[/b] A role is an ordered list of jobs (whole work types like Cooking or single jobs like Smelting). A colonist's roles combine into one clear work order: earlier roles win, and within a role, earlier jobs win. If no role mentions a job, the colonist never does it.
[*][b]No Setup:[/b] Seeds pre-made roles covering every vanilla and official DLC work type. Auto-assigns roles to match existing priorities.
[*][b]Overlapping Roles:[/b] The same job can live in multiple roles, and a colonist can hold both. Assign [i]Emergency Harvester[/i] to half the colony at high priority but disabled, and when blight or a cold snap hits, one click re-tasks everyone to the fields.
[*][b]Easy Switching:[/b] Toggle any role globally or per colonist, without touching the underlying assignments. No more remembering what priorities colonists used to have.
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mnmr/rw.workroles/main/images/feature-toggles.png[/img]
[*][b]Modded Jobs:[/b] Work types and jobs added by other mods appear automatically, no compatibility patches needed.
[*][b]Rules Engine:[/b] Configure roles to only be enabled at certain times of day or at specific locations (settlements, the gravship, caravans).
[*][b]Bill Support:[/b] Configure work bills to be restricted to a particular role. Useful when a bill requires multiple skills, e.g. Leaf Roller (crafting + cooking) vs Drug Maker (crafting + intellectual).
[*][b]Deep Job Control:[/b] The role editor provides a filterable job tree. Jobs within a role can be freely reordered. All of the seeded roles can be edited or removed.
[*][b]Role Groups:[/b] Organize the role list into named, collapsible groups (drag to move or reorder). Roles with rules gather under Auto-Roles automatically.
[*][b]Smart Recommendations:[/b] A per-colonist panel suggests roles from burning passions, gene aptitudes, colony-best skills, training opportunities and colony needs.
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mnmr/rw.workroles/main/images/feature-advisor.png[/img]
[*][b]Powerful UI:[/b] Grouping, sorting, filtering, drag & drop, key bindings, tooltips, customizable role chip display - whatever you need and it should be there.
[*][b]Import/Export:[/b] Easily share or backup your role setup. Import allows overwrite or merge.
[*][b]Multiplayer Support:[/b] Fully RimWorld Multiplayer compatible.
[*][b]Translation Ready:[/b] All text resources are read from resource files.
[*][b]Designed for Performance:[/b] Work priorities are cached; auto-roles recompute every in-game hour (every 2500 ticks).
[/list]

[h1]Worth Noting[/h1]
[list]
[*][b]Seeded Roles:[/b] An initial role set is seeded into the game, covering all detected work types and jobs.
[*][b]Combo Roles:[/b] Various roles (Basics, Farmer, Grunt) that combine multiple work types to make work assignment easier.
[*][b]Blocker Roles:[/b] Used to specify things that pawns will never do (for jobs in any subsequent role assignment).
[*][b]Extra Roles:[/b] Training roles that enable role progression and convenience roles to make prioritization easier.
[*][b]Modded Jobs:[/b] Jobs added by mods are unassigned by default; the role editor warns when a job isn't in any role. AllowTool jobs are assigned automatically (Haul urgently to Basics, Finish off to Herder/Hunter).
[/list]

[h1]How It Works[/h1]
[list]
[*]Each colonist's ordered roles compile into one strict job order: earlier (enabled) roles win, and within a role, earlier jobs win; a job that appears in several of a colonist's roles keeps its earliest position.
[*]The compiled order is fed to the game through the same lists vanilla's job selection already consumes, so pawn AI behaves exactly as it would with a hand-tuned priority grid.
[*]Emergency jobs (firefighting, urgent tending) go to the game's emergency work pass when any assigned role covers them.
[*]Other mods that read priorities get the values WorkRoles computed; priority writes are owned by WorkRoles for managed pawns (which is why priority-setting mods don't mix).
[*]Role priorities are continuously mirrored into vanilla's 0-4 priority map, so uninstalling hands the vanilla Work tab back with your roles converted to priorities.
[/list]

[h1]Recommendation Logic[/h1]
[list]
[*][b]Colony Needs:[/b] Keeps essential roles covered using customizable minimum assignments.
[*][b]Suggestions:[/b] Uses passions, genes, traits, skills/expertise and training paths; armed pawns also get skill-tiered Hunting recommendations.
[*][b]Applying:[/b] Cherry-pick for one colonist or preview and apply colony-wide. Pin assignments that must stay untouched.
[*][b]Protected:[/b] Auto-roles, pinned roles and blockers are never suggested, moved or removed.
[*][b]Genetics:[/b] Fire-fearing pawns get Pyrophobe before Core.
[*][b]Full Spec:[/b] See [url=https://github.com/mnmr/rw.workroles#readme]README[/url] for full details.
[/list]

[h1]Compatibility[/h1]
[list]
[*][b]Save Compatible:[/b] Safe to add to existing saves (priorities convert to roles) and safe to remove (the vanilla Work tab comes back sensibly populated).
[*][b]Vanilla Skills Expanded / Alpha Skills:[/b] Expertise and passions are recommendation signals.
[*][b]More Than Capable:[/b] Hated work becomes an Awful recommendation signal and is flagged on assigned roles.
[*][b]Colony Groups:[/b] Pawn groups appear in the colonist table's Group dropdown.
[*]Tested alongside Better Workbench Management, AllowTool, PUAH+, Common Sense and many others.
[*]Multiplayer compatible.
[*]Requires [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2009463077]Harmony[/url].
[/list]

[h1]Known Incompatible[/h1]
[list]
[*][b]Work Tab Mods:[/b] Not compatible with other mods that replace the Work tab (Fluffy's Work Tab forks, Better Work Tab, Enhanced Work Tab, among others).
[*][b]Priority-Setting Mods:[/b] Anything that uses SetPriority to control job priorities will not work with this mod (e.g. Free Will, PriorityMaster).
[*]If you've tested and found WorkRoles to be incompatible with another mod, let me know so I can add it here.
[/list]

[h1]Specific Mods[/h1]
These are mods I've checked for compatibility:
[list]
[*][b]Colony Groups:[/b] Works (and its groups show up in the colonist table's Group dropdown), but avoid its group work-priority presets (they set priorities).
[*][b]Complex Jobs:[/b] Moves jobs to new work types - should work fine.
[*][b]Keep Building:[/b] Auto-creates work bills - should work fine (no public source, so cannot verify that it doesn't also try to set priorities).
[/list]

[h1]Disclaimer[/h1]
This was created with the help of Claude Code. Since this is controversial (and more than I'd have thought), let me just say that I've worked as a C# developer since it was released (yes, that old).
I do backend/web development, and it was pretty invaluable to get help with RimWorld UI widgets and not having to hand-roll System.Drawing calls (if you don't know what that is, just think of something painful). 
The mod is free and was created in my spare time, and without AI it likely wouldn't exist.

